Column Transformer allows applying separate transformations to numerical and categorical columns in a single pipeline, 
making machine learning workflows cleaner, scalable, and production-ready.

🚀 Objectives
Understand the concept of Column Transformer.
Apply different preprocessing techniques to different columns.
Handle numerical and categorical data efficiently.
Build a reusable preprocessing pipeline for machine learning projects.
Improve workflow automation and reduce preprocessing errors.

🔑 Key Concepts Covered
1. Numerical Data Transformation
Feature Scaling
Standardization
Data Normalization

2. Categorical Data Transformation
One-Hot Encoding
Ordinal Encoding
Label Encoding 

3. Column Transformer
Applying multiple transformations simultaneously
Selecting columns based on data type
Creating preprocessing pipelines

4. Machine Learning Pipeline Integration
Combining preprocessing and modeling steps
Improving code readability and maintainability
Reducing data leakage

📊 Steps Followed:
Load Dataset
Identify Numerical and Categorical Features
Apply Appropriate Transformations
Create Column Transformer
Fit and Transform Data
Integrate with Machine Learning Pipeline
Evaluate Processed Data


